<TITLE> City IT Fair kicks off </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com)The country's largest computer and accessories exhibition, the 'City IT Fair 2010', kicked off at BCS Computer City on Thursday with a colourful ceremony. Finance minister AMA Muhith, inaugurating the event as the chief guest, expressed his pleasure to see the advancements made by businessmen in popularising and spreading information technology. He said the government's vision of a 'Digital Bangladesh' aimed at peace and prosperity for the country. Bangladesh Computer Samity (BCS) president Mostafa Jabbar, however, called for soft loans facilities for small and medium IT businesses. Jabbar, also an entrepreneur, also wanted to see an increase in allocation of the Equity and Entrepreneurship Fund to help boost the industry. The ninth City IT Fair to be held at the 125,000 sq ft Computer City will exhibit personal computers, laptops and all related accessories, from 10am to 7pm daily, up to Feb 8. The 157 stalls at the city, with another 30 situated outside, are offering special discounts for the fair, which also includes gaming and digital photography competitions, quizzes, discussion, debate and more. Raffle draws will be held on entry tickets everyday, while school going children and the handicapped will enjoy free entry. Tickets are Tk 10 each. 
